http://www.allheadlinenews.com/articles/7007504139&cid AHN | Guantanamo Bay Prisoner Dies In Apparent Suicide | news for the digital world Guantanamo Bay Prisoner Dies In Apparent Suicide a.m. EST Mary K. Brunskill - AHN Staff Writer San Juan, Puerto Rico (AHN) - A Saudi Arabian inmate at Guantanamo Bay prison was found dead in an apparent suicide Wednesday, the U.S. military's Southern Command said in a statement. The military did not identify the prisoner's name or exactly how he died. "The detainee was found unresponsive and not breathing in his cell by guards," the statement read. Critics of the prison camp said suicides are not surprising considering Guantanamo's treatment of its prisoners. Detainees at the camp are not able to access U.S. civilian courts and spend up to 22 hours a day isolated in their cells. AP quotes Michael Ratner, president of the Center for Constitutional Rights, as saying, "You have five and a half years of desperation there with no legal way out. Sadly, it leads to people taking their own lives." On June 10, 2006, three Guantanamo prisoners hanged themselves with bed sheets. Since then authorities at the camp have tried to avoid suicides by taking sheets away during the daytime and preventing access to light fixtures. Copyright © AHN Media Corp - All rights reserved. Redistribution, republication. syndication, rewriting or broadcast is expressly prohibited without the prior written consent of AHN. © 2007 by AHN Media Corp.
