sident Bush and Governor Kathleen Blanco to do more to help speed the city's recovery. He said Bush has failed to move federal aid to "the people who need it the most." And he said the president should forgive millions of dollars in disaster loans the city took out after the storm to help it to continue operating. A White House spokeswoman said the city, not the federal government, must be the force behind the recovery effort. Nagin also called on Blanco to use a state budget surplus to help the city. Copyright 2007 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed. All content &copy; Copyright 2000 - 2007 WorldNow and KTRV. All Rights Reserved. For more information on this site, please read our
