nas and Georgia Saturday night as Barry tracks northward close to the coast, including locations such as , and that an inch or two may fall in places farther west including Along with the rain, there will be thunderstorms, some of which could become severe to the east of the track of Barry's center. Southern Expert discusses the threat of damaging winds and tornadoes in his latest blog entry. Barry will continue moving northward over the next couple of days close to the East Coast. Rain will spread into the Mid-Atlantic states through Sunday, which will impact outdoor events in the region, as discussed in the . The rain may be heavy enough to cause some local flooding problems as well. Also, places along the immediate coast will experience gusty winds, but the winds are not likely to be strong enough to cause any damage. As discussed in the , Barry's track will take the heavy rain northward through the big cities of the Interstate 95 Corridor including including Sunday night into Monday morning, then into northern New England during the day Monday. Top Weather News Recent Stories View Most Recent Headline Tropical Storm Barry is Born Helpful Florida Rain; Threatening Plains Storms Florida Rain; Plains Storms More Plains Rain; Tropical Rain Targets Florida Plains Pounding and Tropical Tempest Still Stormy on the Plains Plains Storm Pattern Continues Severe Storms, Floods Continue This Map is Clickable Visit the Maps Center Visit the Severe Weather Center Visit the Travel Center Visit the Maps Center Visit the Maps Center World Weather "Hot Spot" Weather Forecasts for Kids! &copy; 2007 AccuWeather, Inc. under which this service is provided. Not a Member? Read all about
