lso, deny illegals access to all social programs who cannot prove citizenship (except medical care for humanitarian and public health purposes). When illegals can no longer work, they will deport themselves back to their home country (and take their American-born children with them). Some public money may be necessary to facilitate this process, which will take several years. But unless our borders are secured first, the immigration problem cannot be solved. Illegals must take their place in line and go through the existing legal immigration process. This process is currently perhaps too lengthy and needs to be improved, but it has oversight and controls already built into it. For those industries that need seasonal help, or temporary and immediate expansion of their workforce to meet production needs, a separate program will be required to systematically, and in a controlled manner, supply the needs of business. This bad immigration bill currently in debate in Congress, if enacted, would bankrupt Social Security and Medicare and is far too byzantine, with little or no oversight or controls, to have any chance at being successful. â Posted by Bill Warren If politicians running for office cannot do their jobs, then why are they running for reelection or an upgrade to the presidency? The past protends the future. â Posted by J. Gilbert How does McCain suggest we defend our borders? Shall we build a fence around the entire southern and northern borders? So far, more people who want to harm us have apparently come into this country legally, and also through the Canadian border. Most people think of the illegals who are here as Mexicans, but there are a huge amount of illegal Canadians and Europeans, unnoticed because they are white. I don&#8217;t dispute that we need security, but, as a wise man once said, &#8220;Those who exchange freedom for security are destined to have neither.&#8221; â Posted by cora THere has been a slient amnesty for 16 years. McCain and Ke